  "abstract": {
    "value": "The extra-ligand-free CuTC-catalyzed C–P cross coupling reaction of propargylic acetates with H-phosphine oxides is reported to afford allenylphosphine oxides. The reaction took place efficiently with diphenylphosphine oxide and electron-deficient di(4-fluorophenyl)phosphine oxide, but less effectively with electron-rich ones such as di(4-methoxylphenyl)phosphine oxide and dialkylphosphine oxides. H-phosphine oxides themselves may serve as the ligand.",
    "source": "llm_from_front_matter",
    "confidence": 0.98,
    "human_checked": false
  },
